                    <span>This has to be the best book I have so far.  Very easily to understand. He is in-depth about every line of code (you will never say "what does that code do?" All of the code on the disk works 100%. I recommend this to anyone wanting to learn C++, even if you have never used it.  And a very big plus, if you need questions you can contact the author and he will help you out.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">excellent intro... only lacking in a bit of info</div>
